        <num>CCRP 360</num>
        <heading>360.  Hearing</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 360.  Hearing
At the time and place fixed in the writ for the answer thereto, the court shall proceed summarily to hear the evidence and reasons adduced by the person in custody and by the custodian.  The hearing shall be held in open court and may be held in term time or in vacation, or on a legal holiday.</p>
        </content>
